<TEXT>
columbia universitys graduate school of 
journalism announced the seven people selected as 198990 
knightbagehot fellows in economics and business journalism 
the fellowships are designed to provide formal business and 
economics training for journalists at midcareer fellows spend an 
academic year attending classes at columbias schools of business 
law and international affairs 
the 198990 fellows are judith burns new york bureau chief for 
commodity world news a craig copetas national correspondent for 
regardies magazine in washington dc linda corman international 
trade reporter for the boston business journal and lisa dietrich a 
producer for cable news network in new york 
also named tuesday were micheline maynard detroit bureau chief 
for reuters news service hannah moore a correspondent for the 
journal of commerce in seoul south korea and ahmad a talib news 
editor of the new straits times in malaysia 
the fellowships are funded by an endowment from the knight 
foundation and by grants from a number of foundations and 
corporations including the olin foundation the philip graham fund 
the chicago tribune foundation the kraft foundation time inc dow 
jones amp co and ford motor co 
the fellowships are named after john s knight a pulitzer 
prizewinning journalist and businessman and walter bagehot a 
19thcentury economist and editor of the economist magazine 
</TEXT>
