the precode practice of denying postpetition interest to 
holders of noncensensual lines while allowing it to holders of 
consensual lines was an exception to the exception for oversecured 
claims from the rule that the running of interest ceased when a 
bankruptcy petition was filed and was recognized by only a few 
courts and often depended on particular circumstances 
