joseph all 23 patrick nee 22 and russell cohn 18 added and 
removed small floats to the submarine to balance it under water the 
crafts nose was too light then too heavy then too light 
after about 30 minutes of tinkering the crew began slowly 
propelling the icarus back and forth with mead providing the legwork 
for the pedalpowered craft 
swimmers on the other side of the pool easily lapped the 
submarine during its first efforts but as navigator cangahuala and 
mead hit their stride the icarus began picked up speed 
the threeday race beginning june 23 off west palm beach is 
sponsored by the ha perry foundation a nonprofit scientific 
foundation created to inspire development of undersea technology 
through education research and experimentation 
the mit entry will be up against 18 other submarines from 16 
colleges or engineering firms 
mead said the mit crew will use ringers or athletes to 
pedal the submarine the subs are wet or waterfilled meaning 
the pilot and first mate will have to wear scuba equipment 
if greek mythology has anything to do with it the mit entry 
could be the favorite to win the competition according to legend 
icarus and his father daedalus attempted humanpowered flight 
while daedalus stayed aloft icarus plunged into the sea 
