us district judge john walker on tuesday severed helmsley from 
the trial of his wife and two others after finding that the 
80yearold hotel magnate cannot assist in his defense because of 
memory lapses and reasoning difficulties 
the judge did not dismiss the 47count indictment against 
helmsley only delayed his trial indefinitely 
but noting that medical experts expect helmsleys mental 
deterioration to continue the judge said for all practical 
purposes todays order will remain the final ruling in the 
governments case against this defendant 
citing several doctors including a courtappointed 
neuropsychologist walker said helmsleys condition had been 
aggravated by a series of slight strokes 
helmsley and his 68yearold wife leona were indicted in april 
on charges they evaded personal income taxes by disguising about 4 
million in renovations to their greenwich conn mansion as 
business expenses 
the couple head a 5 billion hotel and realestate empire 
just as no man by position of wealth stands above the law 
walker said so too will no man who is unfit to stand trial be 
subjected to a trial simply because the publics interest in his 
case is great or simply because some people may erroneously 
conclude that the system enables a wealthy man to avoid the 
consequences of his conduct 
