wellreceived in this country where public opinion has tended to 
believe that gorbachevs reforms and less bellicose attitude are 
genuine and hopeful signs 
there is no assurance that reforms now under way in the soviet 
union the east bloc countries or in china will succeed repression 
may return 
but whatever happens the people in communistdominated countries 
never again will be as docile or submissive as they have been for 
the past 70 years in the ussr and the past 40 years in china 
bush is right in encouraging these reforms he is right in 
challenging soviet leaders to reduce armaments to a level that makes 
sense for defense but drastically reduces offensive capability 
