prime minister benazir bhutto of pakistan told 
a joint meeting of congress today that pakistan does not possess a 
nuclear weapon will not build one and will not provoke a nuclear 
arms race on the indian subcontinent 
ms bhutto made her pledge in an address in which she said 
democracy is on the rise in her region and dictators are in retreat 
around the world 
she said the united state and pakistan represent a partnership 
for democracy that must redouble its efforts to bring a broadbased 
democratic government to warscarred afghanistan 
pakistan and the united states have traveled a long road with 
afghanistan in quest of self determination the pakistani prime 
minister said 
she said that now that soviet forces have withdrawn let us not 
leave with indifference we must not abandon the cause 
turning to the most active concern voiced in the united states 
about her countrys conduct ms bhutto said pakistan has no 
intention of becoming a nuclear weapons power 
i can declare that we do not possess nor do we intend to make a 
nuclear device the pakistani prime minister said 
she said her government is ready to accept international 
safeguards on its nuclear materials and reactors on a 
nondiscriminatory regional basis 
pakistan has long advocated a nuclearfree zone in the region 
ms bhutto said adding that her country is prepared to conclude a 
nuclear test ban with neighbors in south asia 
she mentioned no other country pakistans regional rival india 
has resisted such proposals unless they include china which already 
has nuclear weapons 
ms bhutto told her audience gathered in the chamber of the house 
of representatives we will not provoke a nuclear arms race on the 
subcontinent 
earlier a senior administration official told reporters that the 
united states has agreed to sell pakistan 60 more f16 fighter jets 
meeting a longstanding request by the moslem nation 
brent scowcroft the presidents national security adviser said 
tuesday night that the deal which was not officially announced was 
complete except for congressional notification he spoke with 
reporters after a state dinner in honor of ms bhutto 
the f16 deal reportedly is worth about 14 billion 
president bush and ms bhuttos talks tuesday focused on the 
bloody conflict in afghanistan pakistans defense needs its 
nuclear program and the international battle against illicit drugs 
officials said afterwards 
the united states and pakistan which has given refuge to 36 
million afghan refugees have cooperated for years in the effort to 
support the afghan rebels seeking to topple kabuls marxist 
government 
with a glittering dinner and a fulldress military review bush 
orchestrated a warm white house welcome for the 35yearold ms 
bhutto who is the first woman to lead a moslem nation and is the 
worlds youngest prime minister 
in his formal farewell remarks bush said he and ms bhutto had 
discussed ways to encourage a political solution in afghanistan 
that would replace the illegitimate regime in kabul with a 
peaceful and nonaligned representative government 
the united states and pakistan will continue to explore any 
serious avenue towards this end bush said 
ms bhutto replied we are in complete accord on the course 
of policy in regards to afghanistan she added that pakistan 
remains committed to a political solution of the afghan problem 
the late president mohammed zia ulhaq ms bhutoos predecessor 
had rejected the idea of a political settlement in neighboring 
afghanistan 
ms bhuttos father was by deposed zia in 1977 and hanged two 
years later zia remained in power until perishing in a mysterious 
plane crash last year that also claimed the life of us ambassador 
arnold raphel and an american general 
bush brushed aside reporters attempts to ask about earlier 
reports of the f16 deal 
an administration official briefing reporters at the white 
house said bush and ms bhutto discussed the f16 sale but added 
that he did not anticipate any specific announcement during her 
visit the official speaking under condition of anonymity 
indicated there were no stumbling blocks to the sale 
the two leaders also discussed efforts to combat drug production 
and trafficking bush said he applauded ms bhuttos tough stance 
on eradicating the opium cultivation and thanked her for 
extraditing an alleged drug trafficker 
after a luncheon in her honor at the state department mrs 
bhutto and secretary of state james a baker iii witnessed the 
signing of agreeements providing for 465 million to help pakistan 
finance housing narcotics and education programs 
the agreements are part of a 228 billion sixyear aid package 
designed to support pakistans economic development according to 
the agency for international development pakistan is the third 
largest recipient of us aid 
