fields between cement blocks where other houses once stood 
at the entrance to the road a homemade sign reads entering 
water pollution area 
the polands ranch house was one of a dozen small homes with back 
yards slanting down to the river lined with trees that in 
summertime blocked the view of the 65acre rayon plant on the 
opposite bank 
avtex fibers inc bought up most of the subdivision five years 
ago when tests showed that groundwater had been contaminated by 
viscose and sulfate bases from the plants holding ponds but the 
purchases stopped short of polands house the furthest upstream 
from the plant because it is outside the contaminated zone the 
