<TEXT>
six days into a bloody crackdown to suppress a 
peaceful movement for freedom the chinese army has failed to pacify 
beijing 
there are numerous reports of clashes between units of the army 
that may be loyal to different political factions 
the massacre saturday and sunday of hundreds of people blackened 
the name of an army onced famed for its bravery and selflessness 
troops once affectionately called brother of the people and 
uncle plaman quickly were termed running dogs and 
fascists by citizens enraged at the killings of relatives and 
friends by their own army 
the events in beijing have raised some questions about the 
discipline and readiness of the peoples liberation army the 
worlds largest army with an active force of more than 2 million 
soldiers 
simple barricades of metal fencing stopped tanks and other heavy 
equipment breaking the drive trains of the vehicles copies of 
1950s soviet models other trucks broke down in the road 
the government announced tuesday that 364 military vehicles 
mostly tanks and armored personnel carriers were burned by unarmed 
citizens 
tear gas used against the tens of thousands of people who came 
out to stop the troops had little effect one canister that landed 
near an associated press reporter briefly made his eyes sting and 
head spin the effects soon wore off 
communications among military units also appeared poor 
on wednesday troops on one beijing bridge scurried behind trees 
concrete fences and trucks as if an attack were imminent the 
assault never came 
on at least two occasions armored personnel carriers driven at 
highrates of speed crushed foot soldiers 
reports of dissension among commanders is adding to the chaos 
on tuesday armies supporting rival factions clashed in front of 
the downtown military museum on wednesday thousands of troops 
moved onto an intersection then retreated as if preparing for urban 
warfare 
troops show a lack of discipline by firing randomly into crowds 
of unarmed citizens 
shots in the air have killed people in highrise apartment 
buildings the windows of one compound housing foreigners was 
riddled by 27 bullet holes wednesday an armored personnel carrier 
crushed at least seven students in a group of thousands that 
retreated peacefully from tiananmen square 
the armys violence has shocked beijing residents 
until the weekend the peoples liberation army held an important 
position in the hearts of many citizens in this capital 
formed in 1927 the army was famed not only for its fighting 
prowess but for its rescue work during disasters and the critical 
help it provided to peasants harvesting crops 
the army goes with the people like fish swims through water 
was a popular proverb 
the pla played a key role in the revolution heeding closely the 
order of marshal zhu de not to steal a pin from the people the 
army gained the affection of chinas peasantry as it battled the 
corrupt nationalists or koumintang and invading japanese 
communist chinas founder mao tsetung recognized this role in 
his famous saying political power grows out of the barrel of a 
gun 
but now the gun has been aimed on the common people 
i lived through the japanese occupation and the kuomintang 
corruption said a 65yearold man never have i seen anything 
like this the army comes from the people how can it kill the 
people 
li tieguo a soldier until last year said he had been proud to 
be a veteran of the army but that turned to horror when he saw 
troops kick a 12yearold girl in the chest and crush her heart 
when i saw these hooligans kill that girl i was disgusted with 
myself he said can these people be my comrades ever again 
the army was one of the four pillars of chinas modernization 
program started by chinese leader deng xiaoping more than a decade 
ago 
so important is the military to dengs planning that the only 
title he has retained is chairman of the central military commission 
under dengs policies the army has undergone a massive reform 
designed to turn it into a professional fighting force it has 
decommissioned more than 1 million troops and purchased vast 
quantities of materiel from the west 
but problems remain 
clashes among units of the army in beijing indicate the army has 
failed to end the factionalism that has plagued the chinese military 
since the warlord period 80 years ago its seven regional armies are 
clearly not all loyal to the same political commanders 
the quality of its soldiers also remains suspect official media 
reports quotes random surveys as saying about onethird of the 
troops are illiterate and say deaf mutes and mental cases have been 
accepted as conscripts 
