president bush said wednesday he will nominate 
michael r deland regional administrator in boston for the 
environmental protection agency as chairman of the presidents 
council on environmental quality 
the selection of deland a 47yearold lawyer who has gained a 
reputation as a strong enforcer of environmental laws brought 
praise from several environmental groups 
the threemember council was established in 1970 to advise the 
president on environmental matters and has few statutory powers one 
of the reagan administraions first acts was a drastic cut in the 
councils staff and the council did little in the eight years of 
the reagan administration 
mike deland is a first rate environmentalist and i think hes 
an outstanding choice said jay hair head of the national 
wildlife federation the bigger question is whether or not the 
president will give him both the resources and the respect in order 
to revitalize rebuild and redirect the ceq 
deland has been mentioned as a possible republican gubernatorial 
candidate in massachusetts and was considered a leading candidate 
for the job of epa administrator earlier this year 
since his appointment in boston in 1983 he has found himself at 
odds with epa headquarters several times for his aggressive 
proenvironmental positions notably on the question of whether it 
would be safe to drill for oil and gas off the new england coast 
during last years presidential race deland added fuel to the 
bush campaigns attack on democratic opponent michael dukakis for 
failing as massachusetts governor to clean up boston harbor but 
while deland criticized dukakis for delaying the cleanup he 
acknowleged that epa under the republican administration also shared 
the blame when bush took reporters on a boatride through the 
polluted harbor deland refused to go along 
in another clash with the dukakis state administration deland 
blocked the development of a shopping mall in attleboro mass 
arguing the complex would destroy environmentally important wetlands 
deland also clashed with then new hampshire gov john sununu now 
white house chief of staff over a proposed development on that 
states loon mountain 
since then deland has supported a proposed moratorium on new 
development on cape cod 
deland is a very strong environmentalist whose selection is 
very much a positive step said david gardiner of the sierra 
clubs washington office 
gardiner and other environmenalists said it was too early to tell 
whether the council which wielded considerable clout in the late 
1970s under president carter would regain influence 
i assume he deland would not have taken the job if he had not 
had some assurances of what the ceqs authority would be said 
gardiner the councils influence largely will be a question of 
staffing and money he added 
deland is a graduate of harvard college and boston colege law 
school he worked for the president of the university of 
massachusetts on the epas legal staff and as a private consultant 
before being named regional administrator for epa unsuccessful back 
surgery several years ago forces him to rely on a wheelchair most of 
the time 
the president has not announced his choices for the other two 
council positions 
