surgery tuesday in which doctors drained a pancreatic abscess 
considered a source of a bacterial infection complicating treatment 
of his widespread organ failure 
marcos suffered cardiac kidney and pulmonary failure may 18 and 
since has been in very critical and unstable condition the pancreas 
helps break down food and produces hormones necessary to regulate 
the bodys metabolism 
the exiled leader remained on lifesupport equipment wednesday 
including a respirator to regulate his breathing tiwanak said 
adding that marcos also undergoes hemodialysis four times a week to 
cleanse his body of wastes 
