the senate passed legislation on wednesday 
speeding 33 billion to veterans programs and a host of moneyshort 
federal agencies setting up potentially difficult talks with a 
house that passed a different version of the bill 
senators approved the bill on a voice vote on the fourth day of 
debate 
final passage came after lawmakers refused to delay for one year 
much of the new medicare catastrophic health care program for the 
elderly the bill now goes to a conference committee with the house 
which passed its version last month to iron out differences before 
the bill goes to the president 
sen john mccain rariz had led a fight to postpone parts of 
the program including a surtax on senior citizens that has drawn 
complaints because of its cost 
his effort was defeated 5149 on a procedural vote in which he 
was opposed by leaders of both parties 
lawmakers however did adopt by voice a nonbinding provision 
offered by the leaders calling on congress to consider making 
changes in the catastrophic care program in future legislation 
