shatner said which was about onethird of what was needed the 
speed may have contributed to bad previews which were reported in 
the press the movie was retooled for its wide release on june 9 
with all of his directorial duties was shatner the actor 
neglected 
interesting he mused if i had been handed this script and 
somebody else was directing i probably have gone in and said 
look i dont think the character is quite focussed 
i might have shortchanged myself as the egotistical actor let 
me rephrase that i dont mean egotistical in the bad sense i mean 
in the actor whose sole point of view is the character 
my job when hired for capt kirk was to keep my focus on capt 
kirk to protect capt kirk to make him as exciting and make him 
move as well as possible he said 
i didnt want to do that with this film i wanted to open 
myself up and make sure the other characters were not only protected 
but a great deal was made of them 
shatner 58 is a canadian born and reared in montreal he 
started acting early 
i began at the age of six acting in camp plays he related 
i continued in montreal amateur theatricals as a teenager i put 
myself through college with radio work i went to the professional 
theater when i graduated from the university mcgill stayed in the 
professional theater through thick and thin ive never done 
anything else but act write and direct 
trained in the classics at the stratford ontario shakespeare 
festival he made his broadway debut in the festivals tamburlaine 
the great shatner became one of the busiest actors in live tv 
dramas won an mgm contract and made his film debut in the 
brothers karamazov 
for a time he bounced between the theater the world of suzie 
wong a shot in the dark films judgment at nuremberg 
the outrage and television for the people 
