in another sign that the chaos may have a widening and profound 
economic impact us banks began reviewing credit to companies that 
do business with china and shortened time limits on new loans for 
trade and investment projects 
were doing something all banks are doing just making sure any 
new commitments and any renewed commitments are kept very 
shortterm three months or less said an official of one major 
new york bank who asked not to be identified by name 
an official of another big new york bank who also requested 
anonymity said its obvious that any sensible countryrisk 
process would be operative under present conditions and commitments 
would be reviewed 
bank of america chase manhattan bank chemical bank citibank 
and first chicago are among some of the prominent us banking 
companies with offices in china many established representative 
offices there after relations were normalized a decade ago 
the banks main role is to expedite financing for joint ventures 
between us and chinese companies but their direct loans to the 
chinese are considered inconsequential and arent reported in their 
accounting statements 
a study by morgan guaranty trust co estimated that total us 
bank loan exposure in china was less than 1 billion 
nonetheless chinas government historically has been considered 
an excellent credit risk and many other foreign banks have loaned 
money to the country 
the institute of international finance a washington research 
organization for commercial banks estimates chinas foreign debt 
